29#include "priv.h"
30#include "ram.h"
31
32#include <subdev/bios.h>
33#include <subdev/bios/M0203.h>
34#include <engine/gr.h>
35#include <engine/mpeg.h>
36
37bool
38nvkm_fb_memtype_valid(struct nvkm_fb *fb, u32 memtype)
39{
40 return fb->func->memtype_valid(fb, memtype);
41}
42
43void
44nvkm_fb_tile_fini(struct nvkm_fb *fb, int region, struct nvkm_fb_tile *tile)
45{
46 fb->func->tile.fini(fb, region, tile);
47}
48
49void
50nvkm_fb_tile_init(struct nvkm_fb *fb, int region, u32 addr, u32 size,
51 u32 pitch, u32 flags, struct nvkm_fb_tile *tile)
52{
53 fb->func->tile.init(fb, region, addr, size, pitch, flags, tile);
54}
55
56void
57nvkm_fb_tile_prog(struct nvkm_fb *fb, int region, struct nvkm_fb_tile *tile)
58{
59 struct nvkm_device *device = fb->subdev.device;
60 if (fb->func->tile.prog) {
61 fb->func->tile.prog(fb, region, tile);
62 if (device->gr)
63 nvkm_engine_tile(&device->gr->engine, region);
64 if (device->mpeg)
65 nvkm_engine_tile(device->mpeg, region);
66 }
67}
68
69int
70nvkm_fb_bios_memtype(struct nvkm_bios *bios)
71{
72 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &bios->subdev;
73 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
74 const u8 ramcfg = (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x101000) & 0x0000003c) >> 2;
75 struct nvbios_M0203E M0203E;
76 u8 ver, hdr;
77
78 if (nvbios_M0203Em(bios, ramcfg, &ver, &hdr, &M0203E)) {
79 switch (M0203E.type) {
80 case M0203E_TYPE_DDR2 : return NVKM_RAM_TYPE_DDR2;
81 case M0203E_TYPE_DDR3 : return NVKM_RAM_TYPE_DDR3;
82 case M0203E_TYPE_GDDR3: return NVKM_RAM_TYPE_GDDR3;
83 case M0203E_TYPE_GDDR5: return NVKM_RAM_TYPE_GDDR5;
84 default:
85 nvkm_warn(subdev, "M0203E type %02x\n", M0203E.type);
86 return NVKM_RAM_TYPE_UNKNOWN;
87 }
88 }
89
90 nvkm_warn(subdev, "M0203E not matched!\n");
91 return NVKM_RAM_TYPE_UNKNOWN;
92}
93
94static void
95nvkm_fb_intr(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
96{
97 struct nvkm_fb *fb = nvkm_fb(subdev);
98 if (fb->func->intr)
99 fb->func->intr(fb);
100}
101
102static int
103nvkm_fb_oneinit(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
104{
105 struct nvkm_fb *fb = nvkm_fb(subdev);
106 if (fb->func->ram_new) {
107 int ret = fb->func->ram_new(fb, &fb->ram);
108 if (ret) {
109 nvkm_error(subdev, "vram setup failed, %d\n", ret);
110 return ret;
111 }
112 }
113 return 0;
114}
115
116static int
117nvkm_fb_init(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
118{
119 struct nvkm_fb *fb = nvkm_fb(subdev);
120 int ret, i;
121
122 if (fb->ram) {
123 ret = nvkm_ram_init(fb->ram);
124 if (ret)
125 return ret;
126 }
127
128 for (i = 0; i < fb->tile.regions; i++)
129 fb->func->tile.prog(fb, i, &fb->tile.region[i]);
130
131 if (fb->func->init)
132 fb->func->init(fb);
133 return 0;
134}
135
136static void *
137nvkm_fb_dtor(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
138{
139 struct nvkm_fb *fb = nvkm_fb(subdev);
140 int i;
141
142 for (i = 0; i < fb->tile.regions; i++)
143 fb->func->tile.fini(fb, i, &fb->tile.region[i]);
144
145 nvkm_ram_del(&fb->ram);
146
147 if (fb->func->dtor)
148 return fb->func->dtor(fb);
149 return fb;
150}
151
152static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
153nvkm_fb = {
154 .dtor = nvkm_fb_dtor,
155 .oneinit = nvkm_fb_oneinit,
156 .init = nvkm_fb_init,
157 .intr = nvkm_fb_intr,
158};
159
160void
161nvkm_fb_ctor(const struct nvkm_fb_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
162 int index, struct nvkm_fb *fb)
163{
164 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_fb, device, index, 0, &fb->subdev);
165 fb->func = func;
166 fb->tile.regions = fb->func->tile.regions;
167}
168
169int
170nvkm_fb_new_(const struct nvkm_fb_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
171 int index, struct nvkm_fb **pfb)
172{
173 if (!(*pfb = kzalloc(sizeof(**pfb), GFP_KERNEL)))
174 return -ENOMEM;
175 nvkm_fb_ctor(func, device, index, *pfb);
176 return 0;
177}
